            <h3><strong>Who We Are</strong></h3>
            <p>International Language Center & Tutoring (ILCT) and James Place work cooperatively together out of the same location on Howell Avenue.  These programs are not distinct non-profit organizations but are programs of churches.  ILCT is a program birthed by Eastbrook Church; James Place is a program started and run by Elmbrook Church.</p>
            <br />
            <h3><strong>Intentions</strong></h3>
            <p>
                ILCT and James Place seek to serve the refugee and immigrant community on Milwaukee's south side.  We intend to:<br>
                ▪ be a <strong>welcome center</strong> for refugees and immigrants; a place where they find a warm, loving welcome from people who are genuinely happy to meet and help them.<br>
                ▪ <strong>build relationships</strong> of love, care and respect with refugees and immigrants; these relationships are to go far beyond simply responding to need in a polite manner.<br>
                ▪ <strong>encourage and equip refugees and immigrants with skills</strong> they need to thrive in the US.  These include English classes, job search assistance, academic tutoring, immigration paperwork, and help navigating the bureaucracies of government assistance, banking, health care, and public education.
            </p>
