            <h3><strong>Mission Statements</strong></h3>
            <p>
                ▪  <strong>Eastbrook Church:</strong> To proclaim and embody the love of Jesus Christ in the city and in the world.<br>
                ▪  <strong>ILCT:</strong> To proclaim and embody the love of Jesus Christ to the refugee and immigrant population on Milwaukee’s south side.<br>
                ▪  <strong>Elmbrook Church:</strong> To help people become rooted in Jesus and released to His mission.<br>
                ▪  <strong>James Place:</strong> Building relationships, responding to needs, and offering hope in the name of Jesus
            </p>
            <br />
            <h3><strong>Values</strong></h3>
            <p>
                ▪ Each person has dignity, value, and is worth loving.  We serve out of love, i.e., from a desire for their best, not out of pity, nor with an attitude of looking down on others.<br>
                ▪ Each person has talents and abilities, and is responsible to use these to better themselves, their families and their communities.  Our best efforts are to encourage and equip people with skills that improve the quality of life for individuals, families and communities.<br>
                ▪ Each culture provides unique solutions to the life problems and ambitions of an ethnic group.  Each culture has strengths, ideas, weaknesses, and unique ways to reflect the Creator's glory.  We look for ways to appreciate other cultures, enhance their cultural strengths, and encourage--gently, humbly--change in areas of weakness.
            </p>
